<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870710-0061 </DOCNO><HL> Sallie Mae Is Offering$46 Million of NotesIn Australian Dollars</HL><DD> 07/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SLMBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Student Loan Marketing Association said it is offering $46 million of 13 1/2% notes due July 16, 1990, denominated in Australian dollars.    The association, known as Sallie Mae, said it will make a separate agreement to eliminate its exchange-rate risk and reduce its cost of funds. Proceeds will be used for general purposes. Sallie Mae makes a secondary market in insured student loans.    Interest payments on the notes will be made semiannually beginning Jan. 16, Sallie Mae said. Morgan Stanley andamp; Co., Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. and Citicorp Investment Bank are managing the offering. </TEXT></DOC>